Mac Setup: Transit Lab
Prerequisites: Install and launch Docker Desktop.
    Clone & Enter:
    Bash

    git clone https://github.com/lkbrennan97/IMT-542-Transit-Lab.git
    cd IMT-542-Transit-Lab

    Build Engine: ```bash
    docker compose --profile ingest build

    Start DB: ```bash
    docker compose up -d fuseki

    *Access dashboard at: `http://localhost:3030` (User/Pass: admin/admin)*

🛠 Execution Commands

    Extract PDF: docker compose --profile ingest run --rm transformer python scripts/extract.py

    Map to RDF: docker compose --profile ingest run --rm transformer java -jar /opt/rmlmapper.jar -m scripts/mapping.ttl -o output/transit.ttl -s turtle

    Validate: docker compose --profile ingest run --rm transformer pyshacl -s data/shapes.ttl -m turtle output/transit.ttl

Mac Notes:
    Permissions: If scripts won't run, use chmod +x scripts/*.py.
    Syncing: Use git pull to get Lincoln's updates; use a Personal Access Token to push your own.
    Line Endings: Ensure VS Code is set to LF (bottom right of window).
